    <item>
      <title>德国商业前景改善远超预期</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/german-business-outlook-improves-much-more-than-expected</link>
      <description><![CDATA[德国商业前景的改善远超预期——人们希望经济能够从导致其成为欧元区落后者的低迷中复苏。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/german-business-outlook-improves-much-more-than-expected</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 22 Mar 2024 09:16:20 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>审计师表示，瑞典 Alecta 老板不对错误投注承担责任</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/sweden-s-alecta-executives-not-liable-for-missteps-auditor-says</link>
      <description><![CDATA[一位审计师表示，瑞典最大养老基金 Alecta 的董事会成员和高管不应为导致 2023 年投资失败损失 31 亿美元的决策承担个人责任。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/sweden-s-alecta-executives-not-liable-for-missteps-auditor-says</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 22 Mar 2024 09:07:17 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>银行无力填补核电 5 万亿美元的缺口</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/filling-nuclear-power-s-5-trillion-hole-is-beyond-the-banks</link>
      <description><![CDATA[随着公众对原子能的支持浪潮日益高涨，核能官员本周抵达布鲁塞尔。银行家在评估他们的雄心壮志的代价时反应不温不火，他们在离开时感到谦卑。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-22/filling-nuclear-power-s-5-trillion-hole-is-beyond-the-banks</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 22 Mar 2024 08:34:42 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
